The reviewers who've given this place 3, 4 or 5 stars are either Columbia students (as a student, their expectations are REALLY LOW),. or locals who are probably used to other disappointing establishments nearby. The Lewinsky is a HORRIBLE sandwich. The chicken was stale, hard to chew, and the oily. To summarize it in a single word, it was DISGUSTING.

Great sandwiches, good prices, and quality fresh ingredients. My go-to's are the hungry man (eggs, cheese, bacon, sausage, home fries) for breakfast and the Cubano for lunch.

They really do have good food here. Never ha e to wait too long & they've added just a couple of vegan things like macro meals, but it's a start. Also, they'll cater to a special request, when possible.
Prices are good and they will accept most forms of payment without a minimum amount needed.
Great customer services n the price is just right...

Take out only

I ordered breakfast & not only did it taste horribly but it looked like they threw old stale bacon from the garbage in my breakfast platter. I ordered ice coffee dark with a splash of half & half which I strongly emphasized & i literally received a large cup of iced creamer. When I called back to complain about my order the man that initially took my order refused to change my order or return my  money. I had to leave my job & walk over to Hamilton deli to dispute my order & ask for my money back. The male worker I spoke to yelled at me & threw a pile of receipts at me then he grabbed my iced coffee & acted as if he was going to throw the coffee at me. I wish I could give them no stars. I WILL NEVER WASTE MY MONEY IN THEIR ESTBLISHMENT AGAIN. Not to mention my coworkers warned about ordering from Hamilton since they've seen roaches in the past & have  gotten food poisoning as well. They not only lost me as a customer but also all of my coworkers as well.

I am not a complainer by any means, you can see that from my reviews but seriously?! There are two single slices of cold cuts on this sandwich. I would hardly call that a hero. Disappointing. I guess that is why their prices are so good? Half the meal for half the price?

Hamdel is a good, late night sandwich shop. I enjoy their chicken sandwiches, including their parm, and the lewinsky. The lewinsky has chicken cutlet with avocado and dressing, and its quite delicious. The bread they use is perfect for the sandwich, and you dont have to worry about old chewy bread here. They have an online ordering system where u can get 10 percent off!
Agree

Hungry Man is the best.

Their hero's really are creative. A large menu of hero's that will have you craving for more. I've tried nearly all of them and they were all delicious. They don't skimp on these sandwiches. They also have a large variety of candy bars, protein bars, chips, and other deli Staples. I go here almost every week and haven't become tired if it. The staff are also very quick and efficient.
They have awesome and creative sandwiches.

This place has messed up pretty every single order I've ever placed. The food is good but the experience isnt the best. Once the lady there gave my order to another person and blamed it on me...the order guy is snarky , the Cook is first class.

This deli is located in the neighborhood where I  was raised. I visit here infrequently for a snack/coffee before heading home to Westchester. I  love the guys who work here, because they are so warm and friendly.
Alright sandwiches, not always fresh ingredients. Good location and hours.

I'm done with this deli. I don't understand how every time I get a sandwich I say "no tomato", and guess what it's in my sandwich. These guys can't seem to listen to simple instructions or they are just ignoring me, either way I won't be returning.

Staff is fast fast fast. Great selection of sandwiches.
Best food in town

Got a burger and it was good with a lot of fries for a reasonable price. But the fruit was fermented: got cantaloupe that said it was packaged two days ago but tasted like it was packaged over a week ago.

Very good food. From the outside it seems to be rundown but the staff was very friendly. I got the twister and the sub was very well prepared and flavorful. When compared to another sandwich establishment like subway, the prices are similar for the a much better sandwich at Hamilton's. Will come again if possible
Friendly staff, amazing sandwiches

The Food is good, if you get what you asked for.  They rarely get my sandwich order correct.  I've been there several times with only below par experiences.
A tad expensive, but thats the area...and everything we have ever gotten here was amazing.  Highly recommended thier sandwiches or the rare gem of finding Nounos Creamery Yogurts...yummmm!!
Fast and friendly service with a small but decent sandwich counter

I just came back from Hamilton deli, quite confused and angry. I ordered a burrito bowl and went to the 2nd cashier (the one in the corner) to pay for it, she charged me and I paid and that was that. I proceeded to wait for my food, and it was ready. The first cashier, yelled burrito bowl and I said yes that's me, she placed it down on the counter and left it there for the 2nd cashier to come and get it and bag it up for me. The 2nd cashier finally comes and says to me YOU NEED TO PAY 75cents MORE!! I said why? She said we charge for the bowl, I said but I told you when I initially ordered that I had a burrito bowl, why not charge me all at once? She screamed at me and cut me off" WE CHARGE FOR THE BOWL", I said that's fine, but why not charge at once, why two separate transactions, what if I didn't have 75 cent cash on me, then what? Would I not get my food? She pretty much dismissed me! I have noticed these cashiers are so nasty and rude. If they don't want to serve customers, then leave, there are tons of people out there looking for jobs. No one owes you anything, you work in customer service so its part of your job to satisfy and please customers! ps. Who charges for a bowl, that is the most tackiest thing I have ever heard!!!!
If you're in the area and hungry, come by get a sandwich.
A Columbia classic. Awesome guys, awesome food, and open late. Highly recommend for a quick bite in the area.

Nice deli to go to,  friendly staff, & once in a while a get a sandwich that doesn't taste good but what happened to their time change?  It's usually open by 645am in the morning on Saturdays but it hasn't for the last month? ? They should always have A second person on hand to cook when the university has class&meets.  Those lines are murder &end up late to work.
A classic spot for salads and sandwiches amongst Columbia students. A bit pricey but very convenient
Cheap deli that is open late near Columbia. Good selection of food that taste pretty good and their beer selection is far from the worst. Many an all nighter was helped along with food from here.
Good sandwiches and prices.

I like their fresh sandwiches, but bought a pre-prepared one today that I had to throw away.  I'm not usually picky and I hate to waste food, but the meat was old.  It was the sciliano sandwich one.  And as always,the males that work there creep and stare and make you feel uncomfortable. I never go to this place for that reason, but even walking by it sucks as they like to stare at your body as you walk by outside.
Great food, fast and friendly service, and delivery is extremely fast if you live in the area (estimated time is 50-60 minutes, usually takes 20). I really like the balboa on a roll.
Nando, Ismael, Roy you guys are the best. Breakfast is always the best.

Great food.  The problem we have is that they do not display credit card $7 minimums charge restriction prominently.  It is posted high above eye view and on side of a overhang.  We did not know about the $7 minimum until after our food had been prepared and we were ready to pay!  We only paid because we did not want to waste food, however any restrictions should be clearly displayed so the customer can make a fair decision on whether and how they want to patronize the store.
Love the consistency! Been frequenting this establishment for 15 years. Sandwiches haven't changed and are as yummy as they always were.

Three of the five times I've been here, they've gotten my order wrong. (This has usually involved putting regular cream cheese on a bagel when I ordered tofu cream cheese, which the menu listed, but which they apparently no longer stock consistently.) It's okay if you just need something quick or simple, but I've given up on them for anything but the direst of bagel emergencies. Also, they're always super crowded.

Overpriced and overcrowded. I pointed out a months-expired orange juice to one of the workers, and just gave the knowing smile/nod and walked away.  However, this is the go-to spot for nearby students, so it does well. Good prices on some items, like coffee.
Delicious sandwiches ....Great employees especially the new cashier she has a great personality and works fast .

The food is most of the time good, but they keep screwing up the order.  They are nice and say they are sorry then I have to wait for another delivery person to come.  But it happens all the time.  If you order from them over the internet call them and confirm that they understand the order.  I had to cancel my order for a full refund because they said it would take another hour to get the delivery person to come back to me again by that time I will be leaving my job.  Now I have to find another place to get my food from thats not going to be screwed up.

Cheap and tasty! Perfect combination for students. The grilled chicken sandwiches and fries are amazing. You also get a your 10th sandwich free which is fantastic. It's usually very crowded which is understandable because of its vicinity to campus but otherwise great stop for a quick meal!

Had a hard time finding this place, normally known as CrackDel for a reason(and unless I am missing something, there sandwiches make you keep coming back and for all I know, maybe they actually have crack inside it cause they are ADDICTING). So many choices, you have to try them all.

I used to go to Hamilton's nearly every weekend for a breakfast sandwich before going on to work, but I've given up on the weekend service. They aren't rude- they're just too busy to get orders right, and I'm tired of getting sandwiches I didn't order, at prices that vary all over the place for the 2-3 things I generally order. Maybe they need to hire another weekend person...?
Sandwiches are okay here. Lots of variety but nothing amazing tasting.

Fantastic Deli - my go-to lunch stop.  Some of the best specialty sandwiches in the city (my fave is the balboa) and you get a free sandwich with every ten you buy.  The service is fast and friendly and the prices are pretty good.

This is a great deli. I love the sandwiches here and the service is always good, but their selection of items (drinks/snacks) are really lacking since the place is so small. Also they tend to be crowded.
